⁸ Obiit enim quarto idus Junii, etin ecclesia Sanctae Trinitatis (quam) ipsa construxerat contra altare sepelitur . , . . autem David filius Sanctae Margaretae . . . . Angliae Henrici primi moraretur nocte . . . . tore sua Matilde regina qua Mat.. . . (MS. Cotton, Tiberius E. i. here ends abruptly). The words after sepelitus, ‘⁶ [Cum] autem David filius,'' eto, are taken by Oapgrave from Aeli-ed of Rievauzae's Genealoyy os the Kinys of Enyland. They are also printed with slight verbal alterations by Surius, and reprinted by Pinkerton, Vitae. Sanctorum scotice, p. 383. 'Phe narrative is also copied by Fordun (l. v., c. 40), as he alleges, from Turgot, and will be found amongst the extracts ascribed to Turgot, reprinted from the Scotichronicon in the present volume.
